She was diagnosed with the disease at birth and has a history of multiple hospitalizations and surgeries due to complications from the disease. Sarah is currently unemployed due to her health complications. The report highlights the challenges she faces with managing her disease and the need for ongoing support and care.

Name: Mary
Age: 25
Gender: Female
Occupation: Unemployed
Ethnicity: Caucasian
Past Medical History: Diagnosed with cystic fibrosis at a young age, she has suffered from frequent pulmonary exacerbations and required several hospitalizations. She also has a history of pancreatic insufficiency and requires enzyme replacement therapy.

Mary is a 25-year-old Caucasian female who was diagnosed with cystic fibrosis at a young age. She has a history of frequent pulmonary exacerbations and has required several hospitalizations. She also has pancreatic insufficiency and requires enzyme replacement therapy. Mary is currently unemployed and relies on her family for financial support. Despite her health struggles, she remains optimistic and determined to manage her condition.
